---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../../css/services.css";
---

<Layout
  title="Education & Training | GeneralSoft UAE"
  description="Professional IT education and corporate training services in the UAE. We offer hands-on training in software development, cloud architecture, and emerging technologies."
  path="/services/education-training/"
  image="/img/og-education-training.jpg"
>
  <section class="service-content" id="software-services">
    <div class="service-section" style="margin-top: 120px;">
      <h2 class="service-title">Education & Training</h2>
      <p>
        Technology is only as effective as the people who build, operate, and
        maintain it. At GeneralSoft, we provide professional training and
        education services that bridge the gap between theoretical knowledge and
        practical, production-ready skills. Our training programs are designed
        for working professionals, corporate teams, and academic institutions
        across the UAE.
      </p>
      <p>
        What sets our training apart is that it is delivered by practitioners
        with three decades of real-world engineering experience — not by
        full-time instructors who have never shipped production code. Every
        course we deliver is grounded in actual project experience.
      </p>

      <h3>Training Areas</h3>
      <div class="features-grid">
        <div class="feature-box">
          <h4>Software Development</h4>
          <p>
            Hands-on training in .NET, Java, Python, JavaScript/TypeScript,
            Angular, and modern development frameworks.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-box">
          <h4>Cloud Architecture</h4>
          <p>
            Azure, AWS, and GCP architecture training including certification
            preparation for Azure Solutions Architect.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-box">
          <h4>Enterprise Integration</h4>
          <p>
            BizTalk, Azure Integration Services, API design, microservices, and
            enterprise integration patterns.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-box">
          <h4>AI & Machine Learning</h4>
          <p>
            Practical ML/AI training covering TensorFlow, PyTorch, LLM
            integration, and MLOps practices.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Projects Proof Section -->
      <div class="projects-proof">
        <h3>Proven Training Delivery — Projects Completed</h3>
        <p>
          Our training portfolio includes university-level instruction,
          corporate knowledge transfer, and professional certification programs.
        </p>

        <div class="project-card">
          <h4>Management of Technology & Innovation — ITU Punjab</h4>
          <div class="project-meta">
            <span class="date">Dec 2019 – Apr 2022</span>
            <span class="role">Instructor</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            Taught undergraduate and graduate business administration students,
            as well as executive classes, a 3 to 6 credit course on Management
            of Technology and Innovation. The course covered technology
            strategy, innovation management, digital transformation, and the
            intersection of business and technology.
          </p>
          <div class="tech-tags">
            <span class="tech-tag">University Teaching</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Technology Management</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Innovation</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Executive Education</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="project-card">
          <h4>BizTalk Knowledge Transfer — 40+ Training Sessions</h4>
          <div class="project-meta">
            <span class="date">Feb 2015 – Dec 2015</span>
            <span class="role">Lead Developer & Trainer</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            Delivered 40+ recorded web training sessions over Skype for
            Business, each approximately one hour, streamed to customer
            personnel worldwide. Topics included BizTalk 2013 R2 migration,
            zero-touch deployment with TFS/Octopus Deploy, SAP integration with
            SSO (Azure/OAuth), and enterprise integration best practices.
          </p>
          <div class="tech-tags">
            <span class="tech-tag">BizTalk 2013 R2</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Knowledge Transfer</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">SAP</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Azure</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Octopus Deploy</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="project-card">
          <h4>Enterprise Content Management Training Manual</h4>
          <div class="project-meta">
            <span class="date">Jun 2007 – Aug 2007</span>
            <span class="role">Architect & Lead Developer</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            Authored a comprehensive 390-page training manual for an enterprise
            content management system serving 22,000+ employees in the
            hospitality industry. The manual covered system architecture,
            content lifecycle management, compliance workflows, and
            administrative procedures.
          </p>
          <div class="tech-tags">
            <span class="tech-tag">Technical Writing</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Training Documentation</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">SharePoint ECM</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="project-card">
          <h4>Academic Lectures — History of Programming & TCP/IP</h4>
          <div class="project-meta">
            <span class="date">1997 – 2001</span>
            <span class="role">Guest Lecturer</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            Delivered a series of lectures on the History of Programming at
            California State University, Sacramento. Gave an IEEE-sponsored
            lecture on Data Communication at FAST, and a seminar on "Insight
            into TCP/IP" at Punjab University. Presented a comparative lecture
            on "J2EE versus .Net" at WOW Sacramento.
          </p>
          <div class="tech-tags">
            <span class="tech-tag">Academic Lecture</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">TCP/IP</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Programming History</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">J2EE</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">.NET</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3>Training Formats</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Corporate Workshops:</strong> On-site or remote hands-on training for your team</li>
        <li><strong>Certification Prep:</strong> Structured programs for Microsoft, AWS, and other certifications</li>
        <li><strong>Knowledge Transfer:</strong> Systematic documentation and training for ongoing team enablement</li>
        <li><strong>Executive Briefings:</strong> Technology strategy sessions for leadership teams</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="faq-container">
        <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
          Common questions about our education and training programs.
        </p>

        <div class="faq-list">
          <details>
            <summary>Are your training programs available online?</summary>
            <p>
              Yes. We deliver training both on-site and remotely. Our remote
              sessions include live demonstrations, hands-on exercises, and
              Q&A. We have extensive experience delivering training across
              geographies and time zones.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Do you customize training for our specific technology stack?</summary>
            <p>
              Absolutely. We assess your team's current skill level and your
              technology stack, then design a curriculum that addresses your
              specific needs. This is far more effective than generic,
              off-the-shelf training programs.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Can you help our team prepare for Azure certifications?</summary>
            <p>
              Yes. Our lead architect has been a certified Azure Architect since
              2017 and holds MCP, MCAD, and MCSD certifications since 2004. We
              offer structured certification preparation programs for Azure
              Solutions Architect and related certifications.
            </p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="contact" id="contact">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="contact-content">
        <h2>Let's Build Something Great Together</h2>
        <p>
          Ready to upskill your team with expert-led training? Get in touch
          with our team today.
        </p>
        <div class="contact-info">
          <div class="contact-item">
            <div class="contact-item-icon">🌐</div><strong>Website</strong><a
              href="https://generalsoft.ae">generalsoft.ae</a
            >
          </div>
          <div class="contact-item">
            <a href="/contact/"
              ><div class="contact-item-icon">📧</div><strong>Contact Us</strong
              ><br />Get in touch</a
            >
          </div>
          <div class="contact-item">
            <div class="contact-item-icon">📍</div><strong>Location</strong
            ><span>Ras Al Khaimah</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
